<package >
  <metadata>
    <id>Flame.Optimization</id>
    <version>$version$</version>
    <authors>Jonathan Van der Cruysse</authors>
    <owners>Jonathan Van der Cruysse</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/jonathanvdc/Flame</projectUrl>
    <!--<iconUrl>http://ICON_URL_HERE_OR_DELETE_THIS_LINE</iconUrl>-->
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <summary>A compiler framework for managed code.</summary>
    <description>Flame is a collection of modular, open-source .NET libraries that can be leveraged to build a compiler. It provides reusable components and a common compilation pipeline, which can be extended with additional passes, to suit the specific needs of source and target languages.

    This package (Flame.Optimization) includes the only the optimization-oriented Flame.Optimization library, and relies on the core Flame.Compiler package.

    If you want to build a compiler with Flame, then I recommend that you also get the Flame.Front package.</description>
    <releaseNotes></releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright 2016</copyright>
    <tags>Flame compiler</tags>
    <dependencies>
        <dependency id="Flame.Compiler" version="$version$" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
